## F17 — GET /api/live SSE route

### Files created

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/lib/live.ts` | `queryNewEvents(sinceIngestedAt, client?)` — queries events after a watermark with identity join |
| `src/app/api/live/route.ts` | `GET` handler — streams SSE via `ReadableStream` + 1-second `setInterval` |
| `src/lib/__tests__/live.test.ts` | 5 unit tests for the query function |
| `src/app/api/live/__tests__/route.test.ts` | 6 unit tests for the route handler |

### Self-evaluation results

| Criterion | Result |
|---|---|
| Test suite | ✅ 259 passing, 0 failures |
| Lint | ✅ exit 0 (4 pre-existing warnings in seed.test.ts, 0 new) |
| Typecheck | ✅ exit 0 |
| Build | ✅ `/api/live` listed as dynamic route |

### Implementation notes

- Watermark is initialized to `new Date()` converted to ClickHouse format (`"YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.mmm"`) — consistent with the codebase convention in `trends.ts` which explicitly avoids ISO T/Z format for ClickHouse params.
- Stream `cancel()` clears the interval, so client disconnect stops polling.
- The "no data emitted" unit test confirms the mock was called (tick fired) then verifies the read stays pending via a microtask-flush approach.
