**Implementation (Step 2):**
- **`useLiveFeed.ts`** — hook uses `pausedRef` (not state) inside the `onmessage` handler to avoid stale closures; buffer is a ref (`bufferRef`) that gets flushed atomically inside `setPaused`'s updater on resume; 200-event cap enforced on every prepend
- **`LiveFeed.tsx`** — connection status dot + "Live"/"Disconnected" text, Pause/Resume and Clear toolbar buttons, empty state, event cards with colored MUI `Chip` per event type, `IdentityChip`, relative timestamp, `JsonChip`
- **`src/app/test/page.tsx`** — placeholder replaced with `<LiveFeed />`

